Item.Name: Adventure Point Gift Shop
Item.Summary: At the centre of the park you will discover the Chessington Shop with an exciting array of souvenirs, treats and gifts. For refreshments and supplies, the Chessington Shop is your port of call between each new adventure.

Item.Name: Adventure Point Hot Dogs
Item.Summary: Escape the hustle and bustle of the Adventure Point and create your own hot dog with a selection of toppings to choose from.

Item.Name: Adventure Point Pizza Pasta
Item.Summary: Venture into Adventure Point Pizza Pasta and find range of pizzas, pastas and freshly prepared salads. Stay as long as you like whilst you enjoy an all you can eat family meal.

Item.Name: Adventure Tree
Item.Summary: The Chessington Adventure Tree sits at the heart of the Park in Adventure Point.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 1.3 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Name: Alaotran Gentle Lemur
Item.Summary: This Critically Endangered species is a native of Madagascar and is the only species of primate to live exclusively in wetlands around Lake Alaotra. They live in social groups with an average of three to five individuals and feed on papyrus leaves.

Item.Name: AMAZU Monkey Talk
Item.Summary: If you have cheeky monkeys, bring them along to learn about our monkeys at AMAZU Treetop Adventure.  After the talk, our Zookeepers will be on hand to answer any questions.

Item.Name: AMAZU Treetop Adventure
Item.Summary: AMAZU Treetop Adventure where young adventurers can play amongst real life monkeys and other amazing animals as you follow the adventure trail through the heights of AMAZU!
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 0.9 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Name: Animal Antics Show
Item.Summary: Exotic animals including Meerkats, Coati, Binturongs and Macaws will come up close and personal to audiences at the Animal Antics Show in The Lawn.

Item.Summary: For your convenience cash machines are available across the resort.

Item.Summary: For your convenience cash machines are available across the resort.

Item.Name: Beluga Whale Talk
Item.Summary: Learn all about Little White and Little Grey and their journey to the World's First Whale Sanctuary!

Item.Name: Binturong
Item.Summary: A vulnerable species, Binturongs can be found in the forests of South-East Asia, where they move slowly through the treetops using their tail like an extra hand. Curiously they give off a scent that smells a bit like freshly made popcorn.

Item.Name: Black Buccaneer
Item.Summary: Ahoy me hearties, get down to Pirates Cove and bring your crew aboard the original pirate ship, the Black Buccaneer. It’s a stomach-churning adventure on the high seas, as you swing backwards and forwards, and higher and higher.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 1 m, then you cannot ride. If your height is less than 1.3 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Name: Bolivian Squirrel Monkey
Item.Summary: Their species is widespread and adaptable to habitat change. They can be found in Bolivia, Brazil and Peru.

Item.Name: Bush Dog
Item.Summary:
Our Bush Dog can be found in Trail of the Kings at Chessington World of Adventures.

See Bandit, the bush dog, settling into his new home in Trail of the Kings at Chessington World of Adventures Resort. He may be small but he is mighty!

Item.Name: Canopy Capers
Item.Summary: This is a sky-high adventure for all the family, as you make your way along bouncing rope walkways, explore the fantasy tree house and see who’s first to make it to the other side.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 0.9 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Name: Captain's Fish & Chips
Item.Summary: Try our freshly cooked cod & chips - a hearty meal for any swashbuckler exploring Pirate's Cove.

Item.Name: Capybara
Item.Summary: The Capybara, native to South America, is the largest rodent in the world, growing to over a metre in length.

Item.Name: Capybara Talk
Item.Summary: Capybaras are proficient swimmers, swimming with only their nostrils, eyes, and ears above the surface. They are also known to swim underwater - sometimes for considerable distances.

Item.Name: Carnivore Talk
Item.Summary: Please see signs in Trail of the Kings to check times.

Item.Name: Carpathian Lynx
Item.Summary: Once common throughout Europe, these shy and solitary cats are now extinct in many regions, but can still be found in the Carpathian Mountains in Eastern and Central Europe. They can live up to 17 years in the wild and longer in captivity.

Item.Name: Children's Zoo
Item.Summary: The Children's Zoo is the perfect opportunity for animal lovers to interact with a range of farmyard friends, including pygmy goats, chickens, KuneKune pigs and sheep.

Item.Name: Children's Zoo Meet & Greet
Item.Summary: Come along and see our gorgeous guinea pigs, sleepy sheep and kind Kunekunes’ who are always pleased to welcome new faces in to their homes.

Item.Name: Dirty Fries
Item.Summary: Choose from your favourite toppings loaded on top of tasty, dirty fries.

Item.Name: Lodge Gate Disabled Toilets
Item.Summary: Toilets with disabled access are available throughout the Resort and are accessible with a RADAR key.

Item.Summary: Toilets with disabled access are available throughout the Resort and are accessible with a RADAR key.

Item.Name: Donut Express
Item.Summary: These donuts are the talk of Adventure Point! Fresh donuts made right before your eyes.

Item.Name: Donut Shack
Item.Summary: Get your paws on fresh donuts made right before your eyes; a perfect treat on your day out!

Item.Name: Dorcas Gazelle
Item.Summary: Native to the deserts of North Africa and the Middle East, these slender animals can survive without drinking, getting all the liquid they need from their diet of plants. They are incredibly fast and can run at almost 80kph.

Item.Name: Dragon's Fury
Item.Summary: This is one very angry dragon and you’re in for a roller coaster ride through dizzying twists and turns, dips and dives and all the while your car is spinning and spinning.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 1.2 m, then you cannot ride. If your height is greater than 1.96 m, then you cannot ride. If your chest is greater than 130 cm, then you cannot ride.

Item.Name: Dragon's Playhouse
Item.Summary: Pint-sized adventurers can have the time of their lives, climbing, bouncing and exploring in Chessington’s huge soft play centre.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is greater than 1.4 m, then you cannot ride.

Item.Name: Fish & Chips Touchscreen Feedback
Item.Summary: We value your feedback! Please fill out one of our touchscreen surveys and let us know about your day.

Item.Name: Flying Jumbos
Item.Summary: They say an elephant never forgets. And you won’t forget this fun flight aboard your very own flying elephant. As you fly around, you control just how high you go, making this jumbo-sized fun for little adventurers.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 1.1 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Name: Go Ape
Item.Summary:
Swing through the trees at one of our two Go Ape courses! Plus, anyone over 1m can enjoy taking park, meaning the whole family can Go Ape together!

Please note, Go Ape courses are subject to an additional charge.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your weight is greater than 130 kg, then you cannot ride. If your height is less than 1 m, then you cannot ride.

Item.Name: Gorilla Talk and Feed
Item.Summary: Please check the times on the board at Trail of the Kings.

Item.Name: Western Lowland Gorillas
Item.Summary: Very endangered in its forest habitat in Central Africa, gorillas are the largest apes and live in groups dominated by a silverback - a mature alpha male with silver-grey hair on its back.

Item.Name: Greater Flamingo
Item.Summary: Flamingos live in colonies often with thousands of breeding pairs, yet mothers can identify their own chick by its call.

Item.Name: Grevy’s Zebra
Item.Summary: This endangered species, now found only in Kenya and Ethiopia, is the largest of all the zebras and like its cousins, the exact pattern of stripes is unique to each animal.

Item.Name: Griffin's Galleon
Item.Summary: Join the fun-loving crew on board Griffin’s Galleon and ride the waves back and forth with an unexpected turn at each end.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 0.9 m, then you cannot ride. If your chest is greater than 130 cm, then you cannot ride. If your height is less than 1.2 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Name: Guest Help and Information
Item.Summary: Chessington's dedicated Guest Help and Information team are here to answer any questions you may have. They can assist with, parent swap passes, height checking, lost children wristbands and much more.

Item.Name: Hotel Gate
Item.Summary: Entrance and exit for guests staying in our onsite Safari and Azteca hotels.

Item.Name: Jungle Bus
Item.Summary: Are you ready for a bus trip with a difference? Great, take your seat on the Jungle Bus and instead of just going along, you’ll swing up into the air for a top-deck view over Wild Asia.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 0.9 m, then you cannot ride. If your height is greater than 1.96 m, then you cannot ride. If your height is less than 1.1 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult. If your chest is greater than 130 cm, then you cannot ride.

Item.Name: Just Chicken
Item.Summary: Enjoy 100% chicken pieces or southern fried burgers and wraps, freshly hand breaded and prepared daily. Eat in or take away, the choice is yours.

Item.Name: Kirk’s Dik-Dik
Item.Summary: These shy animals are small antelopes weighing around 7 kg when fully grown. Originating in Eastern and South-Western Africa, they mate for life and get their name from the distinctive ‘dik-dik’ alarm call they make when they are threatened.

Item.Name: KOBRA
Item.Summary: Rising from the ruins of Wild Asia, the untamed KOBRA takes you on a thrilling ride, spinning through the air as you travel backwards and forwards on a 90 metre track at an awesome 43mph. Adventurers beware, this is a ride with some serious bite.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 1.2 m, then you cannot ride. If your chest is greater than 130 cm, then you cannot ride.

Item.Name: Asiatic Lions
Item.Summary: Smaller than its African cousin, the Asiatic Lion was almost hunted to extinction but now some 350 live in India’s Gir Forest National Park. Males are much bigger than females and have a distinctive big mane and a roar that can carry for five miles.

Item.Name: Lodge Gate
Item.Summary: Park entrance and exit for those arriving via public transport or parking in a tarmac car park.

Item.Name: Lorikeet Lagoon
Item.Summary: Go truly wild on an expedition through the Lorikeet Lagoon, part of Wild Asia... a beautiful way to meet these exotic and colourful birds.

Item.Name: Meerkats
Item.Summary: Nothing to do with a ‘cat’, this appealing animal is in fact a mongoose. They live in underground burrows in large groups and when out hunting several animals will stand on their hind legs looking out for predators and giving a warning signal.

Item.Name: Monkey Swinger
Item.Summary: Whatever your age, bring out your inner cheeky little monkey on this fun ride that will have you swinging through the air, soaring round and round, getting higher and higher. Choose your seat carefully… you could get very wet.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 1.2 m, then you cannot ride. If your chest is greater than 115 cm, then you cannot ride.

Item.Name: Monkey Walkthrough
Item.Summary: Come to our Monkey Walkthrough, where you can see a variety of different animals up close.

Item.Name: Nitrogenie
Item.Summary: Enjoy the world's best ice cream made with the magic of liquid nitrogen.

Item.Name: Original Sandwich Company
Item.Summary: Tuck into handmade sandwiches prepared daily using only the freshest ingredients, add a cup of Rainforest Alliance coffee and that should fill a gap before your next adventure.

Item.Name: Ostrich
Item.Summary: The largest of all the birds (and laying the biggest eggs), the flightless ostrich relies on its running speed of up to 70kph to escape danger.

Item.Name: Otter Talk and Feed
Item.Summary: At Chessington, we have a successful breeding family of otters, with parents Lancelot and Mina taking charge. If you fancy learning more about our loveable otter family, why not come along to our Otter Presentation and feed.

Item.Name: Asian Short-Clawed Otter
Item.Summary: Vulnerable in their natural habitat, these are the smallest species of otter in the world and are perfectly at home on land or in water. They live in extended family groups and younger family members help to raise their little brothers and sisters.

Item.Name: Penguin Bay
Item.Summary: Get up close to our Humboldt penguins in their South American Bahía Pingüino (Penguin Bay).

Item.Name: Penguin Talk & Feed
Item.Summary: Humboldt Penguins are a warm weather species that live off the coasts of Chile & Peru in South America. Come and join our Zoo Keepers for our fun, fact-filled talks.

Item.Name: Pizza Pasta Touchscreen Feedback
Item.Summary: We value your feedback! Please fill out one of our touchscreen surveys and let us know about your day.

Item.Name: Rameses Revenge
Item.Summary: Prepare for a soaking on this thrilling ride that turns you upside down, spins you around and just when you thought Rameses had got his revenge, lowers you down head first over splashing water fountains.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 1.4 m, then you cannot ride. If your height is greater than 1.96 m, then you cannot ride. If your chest is greater than 130 cm, then you cannot ride.

Item.Name: Rattlesnake
Item.Summary: This is a right rattling rollercoaster ride and you’ll be in hiss-sterics as you snake your way through the sharp turns, inclines and sudden dips of the old Mexican tin mine. Life sure has its ups and downs for adventurers.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 1.4 m, then you cannot ride. If your height is greater than 1.96 m, then you cannot ride. If your chest is greater than 130 cm, then you cannot ride.

Item.Name: Ray Talk and Feed
Item.Summary: Watch one of nature's most graceful creatures feed in our SEA LIFE centre.

Item.Name: Reindeer
Item.Summary: Known as Caribou in America, reindeers live in the cold north, including the Arctic. They have thick coats to keep them warm, flat hooves that act as snow shoes and both males and females re-grow their amazing long antlers every year.

Item.Name: Room on the Broom - A Magical Journey
Item.Summary: Visit the enchanted library and walk-through the pages of the book written by Julia Donaldson and illustrated by Axel Scheffler and experience the much-loved children’s story come to life!
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 0.01 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Summary: The Scorpion Express rollercoaster is a fun ride for all the family and brave young adventurers can experience their first rollercoaster thrill.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 0.9 m, then you cannot ride. If your height is greater than 1.96 m, then you cannot ride. If your height is less than 1.1 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult. If your chest is greater than 130 cm, then you cannot ride.

Item.Name: Sea Dragons
Item.Summary: We’ve tamed these friendly Sea Dragons so that little adventurers can hop on board a boat and enjoy a gentle ride round and round on the high seas.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 1.1 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Name: SEA LIFE Shop

Item.Name: Sea Lion Show
Item.Summary: At Sea Lion Bay we have 4 Californian Sea Lions splashing about in the water – 2 boys and 2 girls – who would love you to come over and see them.

Item.Name: Seastorm
Item.Summary: Beware adventurers, there’s a gale warning in Pirates Cove. So get the family all aboard Seastorm and ride it out, twisting and turning over the ‘waves’ in your miniature pirate galleon.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 0.9 m, then you cannot ride. If your height is less than 1.1 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Summary: Come close and learn all about our sharks in the magical SEA LIFE centre!

Item.Name: Smokehouse BBQ & Bar
Item.Summary: Featuring low & slow roasted pulled pork, beef brisket, pork ribs and chicken, all cooked in a wood barbecue pit and smoked to perfection, it will be sure to have you coming back for more.

Item.Name: Spider Monkey
Item.Summary: Spider Monkey can be found in Ecuador. Their diet consists of 90% fruit and 10% nuts and seeds. They are very chatty and like to live in big groups of up to 35 monkeys but split up during the day to find food.

Item.Name: Sweet Shop
Item.Summary: More sweets then you could ever imagine all under one roof! Create your own Pick & Mix selection from the huge variety at Chessington’s very own Sweet Shop. Choose from candy floss, ice cream, bubble gum, popcorn and many more sweets and treats!

Item.Name: Temple of Mayhem
Item.Summary: Located in the ancient ruins of Wild Asia, the Temple of Mayhem is a two-storey house of adventure where you can explore, run wild and shoot your fellow adventurers as they make their own way through the temple.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your age is less than 4 years, then you cannot ride. If your height is greater than 1.4 m, then you must be accompanying children.

Item.Name: Temple Restaurant & Bar
Item.Summary: A unique and interactive dining experience set in the heart of a mystical ancient temple, where a fountain that was once the life force of the jungle is protected by the wildlife that call it home.

Item.Name: The Coffee Hut
Item.Summary: Sip our delicious Rainforest Alliance coffee and why not treat yourself from a selection of scrumptious cakes, muffins and freshly handmade sandwiches.

Item.Name: The Gruffalo Groove
Item.Summary: Journey with other Chessington Adventurers at The Gruffalo Arena through the deep dark wood and encounter some familiar creatures along the way through song and dance. Keep your eyes peeled for an appearance from the Gruffalo himself!

Item.Name: The Gruffalo Meet and Greet
Item.Summary: Located in the Gruffalo Arena, come face to face with The Gruffalo at this meet and greet opportunity!

Item.Name: The Gruffalo River Ride Adventure
Item.Summary: Join your favourite Gruffalo character Mouse on a magical riverboat journey through the deep dark wood.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 1.1 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Name: Tuk Tuk Turmoil
Item.Summary: Tuk tuks are the nippy little auto-rickshaws that cram the streets of Bangkok and this is Chessington’s version. You’re in control as you chase fellow adventurers around, but watch out for others coming at you from all sides.
Item.RestrictionSummary: If your height is less than 0.9 m, then you cannot ride. If your height is less than 1.3 m, then you must be accompanied by an adult.

Item.Name: Vampire
Item.Summary: Just like a bat out of hell, this family-friendly rollercoaster (height restriction only 1.1 metres) gets you soaring through the skies and flying over the treetops with your legs dangling below you.

Item.Name: Vampire's Burger Kitchen
Item.Summary: Visit Vampire’s Burger Kitchen and sink your teeth into our succulent burgers. We are all about delivering the best quality burger everytime you visit, this is why we only use 100% beef & chicken breast.

Item.Name: VIP Experiences
Item.Summary: VIP experiences are designed to make even your wildest dreams come true. From Behind the Scenes Tours, Birthday Parties or Giraffe Feeding you can book your adventures here!

Item.Name: Wild Learning Centre
Item.Summary: Our individual blend of animals and theme park rides truly offers a plethora of learning opportunities - whether you are covering topics like conservation and classifications or even Marketing and Business Studies.

Item.Name: Wild Woods
Item.Summary: We are proud to be the first Theme Park in England to offer a Changing Places toilet, which can be found in Wild Woods. We aim to provide a hygienic, dignified place for people with profound disabilities and their carers to use.

Item.Name: Zafari Bar & Grill
Item.Summary: Our African themed restaurant at the Chessington Safari Hotel. Choose from a range of international specialities fresh from the grill.

Item.Name: ZUFARI: Ride into Africa!
Item.Summary: ZUFARI – Ride into Africa! Is a theme park adventure and safari combined. Come face to face with wonderful African animals such as White Rhino, Giraffe and Grevy’s Zebra as you embark on a thrilling off-road truck journey…
